'''John M. Adam''' was a British [[sailing (sport)|sailing]] competitor at the [[1908 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="Olympic.org" /><ref name="Sailing.org sailor" />
He was a crew member on the ''Mouchette'' which finished second of two teams competing in the [[Sailing at the 1908 Summer Olympics – 12 metre class|12 metre class]].<ref name="Official Report 1908" /><ref name="Sailing.org race" /> At the time, only the [[helmsman]] and mate were awarded silver medals, while the crew received bronze medals.<ref name="Official Report 1908" /> However, Adam is credited as having received a silver medal in the official Olympic database.<ref name="Olympic.org" />
